Below is a pseudocode to help you handle Connection Timeout Exception in WebSphere Application Server: 
//Initialise a user transaction
javax.transaction.UserTransaction tran = getSessionContext().getUserTransaction();
boolean retry = false;
int retryCount = 0;
java.sql.Connection conn = null;
java.sql.PreparedStatement ps = null;

do {
try {
  tran.begin();
  conn = ds.getConnection();
  conn.setAutoCommit(false);
  ps = conn.prepareStatement("UPDATE STUDENTS SET grade = 'A' where id=4342"); 
  ps.executeUpdate();
  tran.commit();
  retry = false;
} catch(java.sql.SQLException sqlEx){
  if (com.ibm.websphere.rsadapter.WSCallHelper.getDataStoreHelper(ds).isConnectionError(sqlEx)){
    try {tran.rollback();} 
    catch (java.lang.Exception ex) {/* handle exception */ }
    if (retryCount < 3) {retry = true; retryCount++;}
    else {retry = false;}
  }else{retry = false;}
} finally {
  //cleanup JDBC resources
  try {if(ps != null) ps.close();} catch (java.sql.SQLException sqEx) {/* handle exception */}
  try {if(conn != null) conn.close();} catch (java.sql.SQLException sqEx) {/* handle exception */}
}
} while (retry);

For more detailed information, refer to the WebSphere Application Server Knowledge Center articles on Connection pooling [https://www.ibm.com/support/knowledgecenter/SSAW57_8.5.5/com.ibm.websphere.nd.doc/ae/cdat_conpool.html] and Exceptions related to data access [https://www.ibm.com/support/knowledgecenter/SSAW57_8.5.5/com.ibm.websphere.nd.doc/ae/cdat_daexcp.html]. These provide helpful insight on Connection Timeout Exception.

The following pseudocode illustrates the procedure to handle a DatabaseConnectionException: 

```
//initialize database connection object and statement
java.sql.Connection dbConnection = null; 
java.sql.Statement dbStatement = null; 

//set retry flag and counter for number of retries
boolean retryAction = false; 
int retryCount = 0; 

do {
    try {
        //obtain a user transaction 
        javax.transaction.UserTransaction userTrans = getSessionContext().getUserTransaction();
        userTrans.begin();

        //Assume a datasource has been created
        dbConnection = ds.getConnection();
        dbConnection.setAutoCommit(false);
        dbStatement = dbConnection.createStatement();
        dbStatement.execute("INSERT INTO EMPLOYEES(EMP_ID, F_NAME, M_NAME, L_NAME) VALUES(1001, 'John', 'D', 'Doe')");
        userTrans.commit();
        retryAction = false;
    } catch(java.sql.SQLException sqlException){
        // If the error signifies a connection issue, attempt a rollback and retry
        if (com.ibm.websphere.rsadapter.WSCallHelper.getDataStoreHelper(ds).isConnectionError(sqlException)) {
            try {
                userTrans.rollback();
            } catch (java.lang.Exception e) {}

            if (retryCount < 3) {
                retryAction = true;
                retryCount++;
            } else {
                retryAction = false;
            }
        } else {
            retryAction = false;
        }
    } finally {
        //cleanup JDBC resources
        try {
            if(dbStatement != null) {
                dbStatement.close();
            }
        } catch (java.sql.SQLException sqlException) {}

        try {
            if(dbStatement != null) {
                dbStatement.close();
            }
        } catch (java.sql.SQLException sqlException) {}
    }
} while (retryAction);
```
